Ray Gunkel https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ray_Gunkel 0 Raymond Fred "Ray" Gunkel (February 16, 1924 - August 1, 1972) was an American professional wrestler and promoter in the state of Georgia. He died of heart trauma after a match in Savannah, Georgia in which he defeated Ox Baker.
